To use the script, open PowerShell with permissions to run scripts. If required, set the execution policy with:

powershell
Copy code
Set-ExecutionPolicy -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned -Scope CurrentUser
Navigate to the directory containing Devil4NessusReport.ps1 and run the following command:

powershell
Copy code
.\Devil4NessusReport.ps1 -InputPath "Path\to\your\nessus\files" -OutputPath "Path\to\save\merged\report"
-InputPath: Folder containing the .nessus files to merge.
-OutputPath: Destination for the merged report file.
Example Command
For example, to merge all .nessus files in C:\Scans\NessusFiles and save the result as MergedReport.nessus in C:\Reports, use:

powershell
Copy code
.\Devil4NessusReport.ps1 -InputPath "C:\Scans\NessusFiles" -OutputPath "C:\Reports\MergedReport.nessus"
After the script completes, navigate to the specified OutputPath to view the merged .nessus report.
